# Mail configuration examples (for real SMTP providers)
# If you want to use a real provider, set these values in your .env (do NOT commit credentials to source control)
#
# Example: SendGrid (use "apikey" as user and the API Key as password)
# MAIL_HOST=smtp.sendgrid.net
# MAIL_PORT=587
# MAIL_USER=apikey
# MAIL_PASSWORD=SG.xxxxxxx
# MAIL_FROM=no-reply@yourdomain.com
#
# Example: Mailgun
# MAIL_HOST=smtp.mailgun.org
# MAIL_PORT=587
# MAIL_USER=postmaster@mg.yourdomain.com
# MAIL_PASSWORD=your-mailgun-password
# MAIL_FROM=no-reply@yourdomain.com
#
# Example: Amazon SES (SMTP)
# MAIL_HOST=email-smtp.us-east-1.amazonaws.com
# MAIL_PORT=587
# MAIL_USER=AKIA....
# MAIL_PASSWORD=YOUR_SES_SMTP_PASSWORD
# MAIL_FROM=no-reply@yourdomain.com
#
# For local development you can keep the bundled mailpit service by leaving MAIL_HOST and MAIL_PORT empty.
